smoothly than seats that were dormant.
Curiously, quite a few hereditary seats had gone dormant over the last few hundred years.
When a seat remained dormant and unclaimed for fifty years, it was no longer hereditary and
moved into the pool for elected seats. The last seat that had converted this way previously
belonged to the Gaunts.
