“Hi Harry,” said Hermione brightly as they made their way over.
Potter had dark circles under his eyes and suppressed a yawn.
“Hiya, Hermione. Hang tight, I have to do the security spells.”
Potter flicked his wand toward both of them, and an odd feeling passed over Draco as though
he was being bathed in something slimy. Mercifully, it vanished a moment later.
“What was that?” asked Hermione, and Draco heard the lilt of academic curiosity in her
voice.
Potter just waved her off. “Polyjuice detection. As long as I know who you are I don’t have
