Draco’s smile fell from his face, and he turned to scowl at her. “Leona?”
“Yes, it’s a carbonaceous asteroid. It’s perfectly in theme.”
“I’m vetoing Leona,” said Draco instantly.
“You keep telling yourself that,” said Hermione airily as she patted him on the arm.
She stepped away to hand Perseus off to her mother, and Draco found himself smiling again,
despite himself. How could he do anything else in the face of his wedding to Hermione
